\newlabel{tab:pareto}{{1}{8}{\color {blue}\textbf {WILT dominates the compute-vs-elicitation Pareto frontier; baselines and ablations do not.} Headline comparison across all method variants on the main-comparison slice. The final column marks each method as Pareto-optimal or dominated; only \emph {Ours: full} sits on the frontier at the high-compute end. A scatter version of this table will replace it in a later draft}{table.caption.2}{}}
\newlabel{tab:pareto@cref}{{[table][1][]1}{[1][7][]8}{}{}{}}
\newlabel{tab:main}{{2}{8}{\color {blue}\textbf {WILT dominates every existing method on all four quality axes (elicitation, fluency, on-topic-ness, diversity) at matched compute.} Main comparison on \PH {Llama-3.1-8B-Instruct}, averaged over the three main-slice behaviours; per-row compute is matched (see Table~\ref {tab:pareto} for the compute axis and Pareto status). Perplexity is computed under a held-out reference model (lower $=$ more fluent); on-topic-ness is judged by an LLM rater on a 1--5 scale; diversity is BLOOM's metajudgement diversity score across rollouts of a behaviour}{table.caption.3}{}}
\newlabel{tab:main@cref}{{[table][2][]2}{[1][7][]8}{}{}{}}
